    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup today is anchored by **Kyle Tucker** (80.03) and **Andy Pages** (69.83), both of whom benefit significantly from a favorable matchup against Chris Paddack. **Kyle Tucker** is our strongest play, bolstered by an elite 15% SP skill advantage and beneficial wind conditions; his ability to contribute across the board\u2014particularly in stolen bases\u2014makes him the pivot point of our offensive efficiency. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (65.71) also commands a start against Suarez, as his high xwOBA and the park factors outweigh the minor drag caused by facing a left-handed starter.\n\nBeyond the core, **Marcell Ozuna** (54.77) and **Miguel Vargas** (53.46) occupy the marginal tier, though their starts are contingent on navigating specific risks. **Miguel Vargas** presents the most concern today; while his matchup against Kochanowicz offers an elite SP skill advantage (+19%), a 38% rain risk and inward-blowing winds have suppressed his upside. The most difficult bench decision involved **Nolan Schanuel** (49.48), who pushed hard for a spot due to a soft matchup against Kay. However, he ultimately fell short of the threshold compared to our active utility options, as his lower batting order position and weather-related headwinds made him a secondary priority. \n\nWe are currently monitoring \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for **Liam Hicks**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, and **Jackson Merrill**. Should any of these players move down in their respective batting orders once official lineups are posted, we will reassess their dynamic order modifiers. **Jackson Merrill** (50.36) remains a cautionary start given the significant platoon disadvantage against Matthew Boyd, so we will be watching his placement closely to ensure he stays above the floor. Stay vigilant on the **Miguel Vargas** weather report as we approach first pitch.",
